From d4b71752a718dad671d9f89081cb841229b5f02d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Santhosh Ramesh <santrame@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 2025 13:39:02 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PROTOCOL:mac80211_hwsim: enable SUPPORTS_EXT_REMAIN_ON_CHAN
capability

Enable SUPPORTS_EXT_REMAIN_ON_CHAN in mac80211_hwsim to fix
remain-on-channel (ROC) failures during DPP authentication.

DPP uses ROC to listen on a specific channel for authentication frames.
Without this capability, ROC requests fail with -EOPNOTSUPP,
causing DPP LISTEN to fail.

Enabling this capability allows ROC requests to succeed and ensures
DPP authentication proceeds as expected.

Patch-dependency:
patches/ath12k/0352-UPSTREAM-CP-wifi-ath12k-add-WBS-support-for-ROC.patch

Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Santhosh Ramesh <santrame@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/virtual/mac80211_hwsim.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/virtual/mac80211_hwsim.c b/drivers/net/wireless/virtual/mac80211_hwsim.c
index 805683c..7d45391 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/virtual/mac80211_hwsim.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/virtual/mac80211_hwsim.c
@@ -5350,6 +5350,7 @@ static int mac80211_hwsim_new_radio(struct genl_info *info,
 	ieee80211_hw_set(hw, REPORTS_TX_ACK_STATUS);
 	ieee80211_hw_set(hw, TDLS_WIDER_BW);
 	ieee80211_hw_set(hw, SUPPORTS_MULTI_BSSID);
+	ieee80211_hw_set(hw, SUPPORTS_EXT_REMAIN_ON_CHAN);
 
 	if (param->mlo) {
 		hw->wiphy->flags |= WIPHY_FLAG_SUPPORTS_MLO;
-- 
